  "description": "The French-door refrigerator by Liebherr is a flagship solution ideal for large families, owners of spacious kitchens, and the most demanding users. The model includes a NoFrost system in the freezer compartment, eliminating the need for manual defrosting. Another standout feature of the unit is the BioFresh compartment, a freshness zone with two pull-out drawers in the refrigeration chamber. One drawer can provide optimal conditions for storing meat and dairy products (Meat & Dairy), while the other is for vegetables and fruits (Fruit & Vegetable). The Liebherr CBNste 8872 refrigerator features an internal MagicEye touch control with a display and flexible settings — from temperature and various mode selections (such as vacation mode) to child safety lock. The freezer is located in the lower part of the body and is split between two separate pull-out containers with practical telescopic slides. One of these drawers contains an ice maker for producing ice cubes. In these two compartments, it's possible to freeze about 10 kg of food per day, and in case of power failures, the cold can be maintained for a total of up to 17 hours. The refrigerator compartment houses four wide open shelves and six door pockets — three on each door. Notable features also include the relatively noisy operation (up to 42 dB), large dimensions (91 cm wide, 203 cm high), and substantial weight (over 100 kg). <b>Key highlights:</b> NoFrost technology and BioFresh zone optimize storage, MagicEye control offers flexibility, and the unit provides significant freezing capacity even during power outages.",
